CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper September 19, 1959, pg. A16, reads: "Mrs. Wynn Entertains - Mrs. Samuel J. Wynn gave a gay luncheon Saturday honoring former Pittsburgher, Mrs. Ella Christian, who now lives in Florida. Some 60 socialites thronged the Wynn home on Iowa St., during the afternoon. Shown are Mrs. Wilbur Douglass and her house guest, Mrs. William Roberts, of New Rochelle, N. Y.; Mrs. Wynn and Mrs. Andrew Brookins, far right. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Six women including Mrs. Wilbur Douglass, Mrs. William Roberts, Mrs. Samuel J. Wynn, and Mrs. Andrew Brookins posed in front of porch of Wynn home, Iowa Street, Hill District
